## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript
    const workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
    // await workbook.xlsx.load(await excelFileBlob.arrayBuffer());

    const worksheet = workbook.worksheets[0];
    
    worksheet.autoFilter = {
      from: {
        row: 1,
        column: 1,
      },
      to: {
        row: worksheet.lastRow!.number,
        column: worksheet.lastColumn!.number,
      },
    };
```

## The expected behaviour:

<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->

It works in LibreOffice as well as MS Office.

We have used another lib (sheetjs) in the past which worked in both
